# 🏷 What is IoC Container?

The **IoC Container** is the heart of the Spring Framework.

It is responsible for:

* Creating Beans
* Managing Beans
* Injecting Dependencies
* Controlling Bean Lifecycle

---

# 📦 Types of IoC Container

Spring provides two IoC containers:

## 1️⃣ BeanFactory

* Basic IoC Container
* Lightweight
* Lazy Initialization
* Less Common

```text id="wjlwm6"
BeanFactory
      │
      ▼
Create Bean When Needed
```

---

## 2️⃣ ApplicationContext

* Advanced IoC Container
* Most Common
* Eager Initialization
* Enterprise Features

```text id="wjlwm7"
ApplicationContext
         │
         ▼
Creates Beans at Startup
```

---

# 📊 BeanFactory vs ApplicationContext

| BeanFactory     | ApplicationContext |
| --------------- | ------------------ |
| Basic Container | Advanced Container |
| Lazy Loading    | Eager Loading      |
| Less Features   | More Features      |
| Rarely Used     | Commonly Used      |

---

# 🫘 What is a Bean?

A **Bean** is an object managed by the Spring IoC Container.

Example:

```java id="wjlwm8"
@Component
public class Student {

}
```

Spring automatically creates and manages this object.

